# FQA maintaining
**1. What is the purpose of requiring my email address? **<br>
Automatic email confirmation of borrowing or purchasing is provided. It is not possible to authorise the transmission of the borrowing or purchasing confirmation. 

**2. Is it open seven days a week? **<br>
Yes, it is visible 24 hours a day. 

**3. How can I add a new function to the LibroX system?**<br>
The system codes can be copied from an alternate (main) repository.

**4. How do I borrow a book from LibroX? **<br>
To borrow a book, first search for it, then click on it to view its details, and last click on the "Borrow" option. To complete the borrowing procedure, you must have a subscription.

**5.	How many books may I borrow at once?**<br>
The quantity of books you can borrow at one time is determined by your membership status and the restrictions of your library. 

**6. For how long may I borrow a book?**<br>
The borrowing duration for a book is determined by your membership type and the LibroXÂ policy. Books may usually be rented for a few weeks or a month, and you can renew your borrowing time if necessary.

**7. How can I renew a borrowed book? **<br>
To renew a book, log into your account, locate the book you wish to renew, and click the "Renew" button. You can renew the book as long as there are no holds on it and you haven't reached the maximum number of renewals.

**8. How do I pay for books purchased using the LibroX application system?**<br>
You can use a valid credit or debit card to pay for books purchased using the LibroX application system.

**9. Can I follow the status of my borrowing and purchasing operations on the application system?**<br>
Yes, you can follow the status of your borrowing and purchasing actions by logging into your account and examining your borrowing and purchasing history.

**10.	How can I reserve a book that is currently checked out by someone else?**<br>
To reserve a book, you can search for the book you want to reserve, view its details, and click on the "Reserve" button. You will be notified when the book becomes available.

**11.	How can I contact the library for help or support related to the online management application system?**<br>
You can contact the library by phone or email for help or support related to the online management application system. The contact information can be found on the library's website or in the application system itself.


